anea Mediaevalia takes an interdisciplinary look at this period while addressing critical, classic evaluations. More than 30 contributions discuss the philosophy of the Late Middle Ages (with special attention to moral and natural philosophy), scientific institutions of the Late Middle Ages, the architecture, economic and legal history, and the spirituality in the Late Middle Ages, as well as prominent figures such as Jean Gerson and Nicholas of Cusa.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aCivilization, Medieval. 0aMiddle Ages. 0aPhilosophy, MedievalxHistory. 0aPhilosophy, Medieval. 4aMittelalter. 4aNeuzeit. 4aPhilosphie. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / General.2bisacsh1 aAertsen, Jan A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAertsen, Jan A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aAris, Marc-Aeilko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeierwaltes, Werner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBenz, Hubert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCourtenay, William J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGensler, Marek, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGerwing, Manfred, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoldstein, Jürgen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrosse, Sven, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHamm, Berndt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHasse, Dag Nikolaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoenen, Maarten J. F. M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aImbach, Ruedi, econtributor.4ctb4http